      "content": {
        "title": "Standard Normal and Z-Scores",
        "definition": "Z-score z = (x − μ)/σ standardizes any normal variable to mean 0, standard deviation 1 for table lookup.",
        "summary": "Z-scores express how many standard deviations a value lies from the mean, enabling probability calculations."
